You are an expert Python pre-press software engineer specializing in print automation. 

Extend our existing Python Flask imposition script (which calculates Grid and Honeycomb sticker layouts on A3, 12x18, and 13x19 sheets) to automatically generate standard industry "Registration Marks" in the four corners of the output file. These marks are required by optical sensors on digital vinyl cutters (like Graphtec, Summa, or Roland plotters) to track and align the kiss-cut paths.

### 1. Registration Mark Specifications:
- Type: Implement standard 90-degree "L-type" registration marks (or solid 5mm circular dots, choose the most reliable geometric vector representation).
- Dimensions: The lines of the L-mark should be 0.4 inches (10mm) long and 0.04 inches (1mm) thick, colored in solid registration black (CMYK: 100, 100, 100, 100 or RGB: 0, 0, 0).
